ita, one=\r\n will find that what Krshna the Guru adviced in the Gita,=C2=A0Krshna the=\r\n=C2=A0Divine Worker=C2=A0himself followed it all through his life at every =\r\ninstance. It is his=C2=A0perfect detachment under all circumstances of life=\r\n, from childhood=C2=A0to his death,=C2=A0that makes me wonder, was this a m=\r\nan or was this a God? Can a man even do something like this? It is as if th=\r\nere is a part of Krshna who is always separate from everything, and silentl=\r\ny watches the whole scene with a bemused smile. He had not a single persona=\r\nl stake in the Mahabharata. Rama at least had his wife abducted for him to =\r\nstart a war against\n&gt;  Ravana. But Krshna had zero=C2=A0personal stake in t=\r\nhe Mahabharata.=C2=A0After liberating his parents from Kamsa, very soon he =\r\nwent off to meet the Pandavas. From out of nowhere he forced himself into t=\r\nhe politics of the Mahabharata, and precipitated a great war to cleanse the=\r\n world of burden. While Lakshmana devoutly followed Rama all along the Rama=\r\nyana and they were like an inseparable pair, as=C2=A0Balarama in his next i=\r\nncarnation=C2=A0he could=C2=A0hardly understand Krshna. There are so many o=\r\nccassions where Balarama asks Krshna, what are they doing with all these ki=\r\nngs, and=C2=A0that they should=C2=A0return to their village in Vrndavana. K=\r\nrshna merely smiles. He knows that not everyone will understand everything.=\r\n But that cannot stop him from following his dharma, with perfect detacheme=\r\nnt from eveyrthing of this plane. Neither false praises, nor wrong accusati=\r\nons by his close people can affect him one bit. And I am not even counting =\r\nthe miracles he perfromed as a Divine\n&gt;  Child. So I worship Krshna, becaus=\r\ne I have not yet met or heard of read of=C2=A0a single sadhaka or saint or =\r\nordinary man or mahatma=C2=A0who has displayed this kind of perfected detac=\r\nhment through thick and thin, yet not withdrawing from the world or activel=\r\ny performing a larger dharma.\n&gt; &gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt; &gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;I started appreciating Swa=\r\nmi Vivekanada more after I understood a bit of the Krshna Avatara. That was=\r\n the last known saint who lived a whirlwind life in the middle of a circus-=\r\nstoplight of fame and accusations, on one side adoring admirers and on the =\r\nother bitter enemies accusing him of=C2=A0being a heretic=C2=A0right upto t=\r\nhe=C2=A0very end of his brief life,=C2=A0and yet none of that affected him =\r\nto any great degree. He faced terrific racism in the America, yet not a sin=\r\ngle speech of his reflects the slightest trace of bitterness, anger, or neg=\r\nativity. That is such a fantastic achievement, IMHO.\n&gt; &gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt; &gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;I a=\r\ngree with you, Narasimha, for most of us it is better to=C2=A0try to=C2=A0m=\r\nould ones life=C2=A0with the same kind of supreme selflessness that Rama sh=\r\nowed all along.=C2=A0Not just worship Rama=C2=A0but more importantly study=\r\n=C2=A0his life and imbibe,=C2=A0to whatever degree possible, the quality he=\r\n represented.=C2=A0Maybe, just maybe, then the Unmanifested Reality - Shiva=\r\n - will fix the mind so firmly on that Reality, that in some future life, i=\r\nn some later birth, one will be able to live life like Krshna showed, unatt=\r\nached and unaffected by any dirt that the world throws up. And then the=C2=\r\n=A0Universal=C2=A0Chit-Shakti (Adya Shakti)=C2=A0will flood such an individ=\r\nual with oppulence unimaginable, of this world and also of=C2=A0what lies i=\r\nn other worlds, like Krshna&#39;s six oppulences -=C2=A0Infinite wealth, infini=\r\nte beauty, infinite power/knowledge, infinite fame, and infinite detachment=\r\n from all the other five. \n&gt; &gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt; &gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt; &gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;Enjoyed this dis=\r\ncussion. :)\n&gt; &gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt; &gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;Jai Jai=C2=A0Rama Krshna Hari!\n&gt; &gt;&gt