&gt; &gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;As collective consciousness became denser, being established =\r\nin Self became less natural and more effort was needed. So the &quot;spirit of p=\r\natience, persistence and\n&gt;  hard-work&quot; (Saturn) became relevant and an avat=\r\nara corresponding to Saturn occurred. And so on.\n&gt; &gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt; &gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;In the =\r\ndark ages of Kali yuga, rational minds wouldn&#39;t accept anything that didn&#39;t=\r\n &quot;make sense&quot;. Being established in Self became an unnatural, ridiculous an=\r\nd incomprehensible notion. So the &quot;spirit of comprehension&quot; (Mercury) becam=\r\ne relevant. An avatara corresponding to Mercury occurred and tried to expla=\r\nin being established in Self as a comprehensible notion, so that rational m=\r\ninds of that age would accept it to an extent and attempt it.\n&gt; &gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;=C2=A0\n=\r\n&gt; &gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;Avataras occur based on the needs of collective consciousness. Of cou=\r\nrse, if one&#39;s consciousness is in a different state from the collective con=\r\nsciousness of that time, the current avatara may not be relevant to one.\n&gt; =\r\n&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt; &gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;*=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 *=C2=A0=C2=A0=\r\n=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 *\n&gt; &gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt; &gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; I respect Rama, but I=\r\n worship Krshna.\n&gt; &gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt; &gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;I am\n&gt;  awestruck by Krishna and worshi=\r\np him, but I see Rama as an ideal that I MAY be able to emulate oneday. In =\r\nfact, I recommend the approach to others.\n&gt; &gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt; &gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;Though I said =\r\nRama and Krishna are almost the same, there is a difference between soul an=\r\nd perfected mind. Soul is a spark of Shiva and a perfected mind is a spark =\r\nof Chit Shakti (whereas an imperfect mind is a spark of Maya shakti).\n&gt; &gt;&gt;&gt;=\r\n&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt; &gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;\n&gt; &gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;