Lord Krishna&#39;s story is a perfected example of how mind operates. Lord=\r\n Vamana&#39;s story is a perfected example of how wisdom/discrimination operate=\r\ns. Lord Narasimha&#39;s story is a perfected example of how energy/drive/initia=\r\ntive operates. =C2=A0 *=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 *=C2=A0=\r\n=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 * =C2=A0 Now, let us remember one basi=\r\nc thing. Soul in us, mind in us, energy in us, learning spirit in us, wisdo=\r\nm in us, happiness in us, discipline/patience in us - all these are differe=\r\nnt manifestations of the same Self. However, when Self manifests as these d=\r\nifferent aspects, it has different qualities and plays different roles. The=\r\nre is no comparison between them. =C2=A0 We MAY focus on\n&gt;  one aspect of u=\r\ns first, perfect it and then perfect other aspects through it. But, we need=\r\n balance between all aspects in the end. Similarly, these different aspects=\r\n of Supreme Being are incomparable and are in a balance working together in=\r\n the Cosmos. =C2=A0 *=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 *=C2=A0=C2=\r\n=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 * =C2=A0 One who is fascinated by the qua=\r\nlities of soul may like the story that demonstrates how soul operates; one =\r\nwho is fascinated by the qualities of mind may like the story that demonstr=\r\nates how mind operates, and one who is fascinated by the qualities of wisdo=\r\nm may like the story that demonstrates how wisdom operates. And so on. But =\r\nthis is just a matter of taste and subjective preference. =C2=A0 *=C2=A0=C2=\r\n=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 *=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=\r\n=A0 * =C2=A0 Let us focus on Rama and Krishna, i.e. soul and mind. Soul is =\r\nseen as a representative of god in us, because of some basic attributes of =\r\nit.\n(Message over 64 KB, truncated)"}}